feat(stage): add SNV scaler binary search algorithm for text fitting

Extracts the binary search font fitting algorithm from presenter-dev1's
SNV scaler feature branch. Key improvements:

- Binary search convergence (O(log n) vs linear O(n))
- Visual line counting using DOM ranges (more accurate than scrollHeight)
- Proper line-height handling (unitless vs px)
- Tolerance-based fitting (FIT_LINE_TARGET + FIT_LINE_TOLERANCE)

The algorithm finds the largest font size that keeps text within the
target line count, using binary search for efficient convergence.

